## Architect Workflow (always run first)

The `architect` agent at `.opencode/agents/architect.md` orchestrates every task:

1. Pre-flight stale-reference check against `discovery/data/*.json`
2. Draft TASK BRIEF: goal, constraints, acceptance criteria, specialists, tools
3. Switch persona to relevant specialist (load from `.opencode/agents/<specialist>.md`)
4. Run peer review (Backend → Security + QA; Frontend → QA; Integrations → Security + QA). **Two-loop max** then escalate
5. Acceptance: 0 CRITICAL, 0 HIGH (or justified), final score ≥ 95
6. Closing documentation: per-app `CLAUDE.md` (or app-specific notes), `CHANGELOG.md`, ADRs

